answerText: Miguel de Unamuno y Jugo [10] An earlier Spanish writer, this man wrote several Novelas Ejemplares as well as a novel about a dude who tilts at windmills and christens a whore Dulcinea, Don Quixote de la Mancha.
heading: ACF Winter |2009 | UC San Diego and Washington University and Chicago B | 5 | Literature | European | College
subject: Literature
question: Question: This writer outlined some of his religious views in his philosophical tract The Agony of Christianity.  [10] Identify this Spanish writer, a member of the Generacion del 98, who wrote about San Manuel Bueno, the titular Martir, as well as about Augusto's efforts to court Eugenia in the novel Mist.
